The PDP Governors Forum (PDP-GF) has appointed Hon. C.I.D. Maduabum as the new Director General of the forum. This is sequel to a resolution of the Forum in June 2019, which was reconfirmed on 26th January 2020. A statement on Tuesday night by Muhammad Bello, the Special Adviser, Media and Publicity to the newly appointed Chairman of PDP Governors’ Forum and governor of Sokoto state, Aminu Wairi Tambuwal, said Maduabum is to work with the Forum in building the party. “He (Maduabum) is expected to assist in repositioning and reorganising the PDP-GF to play its role in nation building under the leadership of the new Chairman, Gov. Aminu Waziri Tambuwal, CFR,” Bello said. He said Hon. Maduabum is a former member of the House of Representatives, a legal practitioner and an experienced administrator. We’ll work with NWC to strengthen PDP, deepen democracy — Tambuwal Few weeks to polls: PDP govs have no arrow head Tambuwal replaces Seriake Dickson as Chair of PDP Governors' Forum